shared_text:
Chazy Junior and Senior High School
June 12 at 4:39 PM ·

The seniors of 2020 have received their yearbooks! We plan on distributing other
pre-ordered yearbooks on the days designated for students to come and pick
up their locker contents, June 17,18,19 from 4-7 p.m.

You may also purchase a copy of the yearbook during those times, even if
you didn't order ahead. To purchase, make a check for $48.60 (includes tax)
payable to CCRS Yearbook Club, or cash in that amount. Steve Patnode will
be at school to handle the transaction.

The yearbook will also remain on sale in the Main Office. Calling ahead to
say you'd like to come in to purchase a yearbook is best, 518-846-7135.
Any questions, please email Steve Patnode, spatnode@chazy.org, or call
518-846-7135 and leave a message. Thank you!

shared_text:
Chazy Junior and Senior High School
May 29 at 6:52 PM ·

Yearbook Update:

The 2020 yearbook (featuring this beautiful eagle cover art by senior Cale Norcross)
will arrive in June! Delivery has been delayed due to the pandemic but
the books should be here in a couple of weeks. As is traditional, seniors will receive
their yearbooks first. Distribution plans will be forthcoming on the school Facebook pages.
If you wish to pre-order, write a check payable to CCRS Yearbook Club in the amount of
$48.60 (includes tax) and mail to CCRS Yearbook Club, 609 Miner Farm Road,
Chazy, NY 12921. Yearbooks may also be purchased without pre-ordering. When
pick-up times have been determined we will make a plan for people to purchase a book via
curbside delivery at school. If you have any questions, please contact yearbook adviser
Steve Patnode, email: spatnode@chazy.org, or 518-846-7135 (leave a message). Thank you!

post_text: For many years Mr. Cory Thompson has been a part of the school family we value here at CCRS. He is a person whose generosity has made a difference in the lives of many and we would like to encourage members of the community to show their support to his family as they navigate this difficult chapter in their lives. Every person who attends will be doing their part to contribute to the medical bills being accrued as a result of Alice Thompson’s illness. Every bit can make a meaningful difference.

post_text: This Tuesday the CCRS School Board was visited by these three lovely ladies. Theses ladies (Susan Goddeau, Julie Fink and Laurie Bell) are the daughters of our former Kindergarten teacher Mrs. Jeanette Miller. The ladies shared the story of how their mother was given this framed picture of the old school by her husband as a gift on her retirement from CCRS. While recently living in the Meadowbrook Healthcare Facility, Mrs. Miller asked that this picture be placed in her room with her. Sadly, Mrs. Miller passed away. Her family wanted to share the story of her love and appreciation for CCRS and of her beloved picture of our school. Her family felt compelled to share the story and to give the picture to the school. We feel so thankful for Mrs. Miller’s love for our school and to the children she taught. It was decided that Mrs. Miller’s picture will be displayed in the only appropriate place….in her old classroom.

The ladies shared the story of how their mother was given this framed picture of the old school by her husband as a gift on her retirement from CCRS. While recently living in the Meadowbrook Healthcare Facility, Mrs. Miller asked that this picture be placed in her room with her. Sadly, Mrs. Miller passed away. Her family wanted to share the story of her love and appreciation for CCRS and of her beloved picture of our school. Her family felt compelled to share the story and to give the picture to the school. We feel so thankful for Mrs. Miller’s love for our school and to the children she taught. It was decided that Mrs. Miller’s picture will be displayed in the only appropriate place….in her old classroom.

post_text: It’s just a start! Here is the beginning of our Outdoor Classroom. With a large donation from the CCRS PTO, we were able to construct an area with edging, wood chips and a few tables. In the future, we hope to have a few more tables and to landscape around the area. It will become an area for teachers to take out their students for instruction or lunch. We also hope community members will use it when they come to use our playground. Thanks again to the CCRS PTO for making this project possible.

post_text: After 15 years at CCRS, Mrs. Jan Davis has retired. She has been a part of the CCRS community for over 50 years as a member of our School Board and Athletic Association, the School Treasurer and most importantly as a Mom. We know we will still see her in her usual spot in the bleachers at all the CCRS sporting events rooting on the Eagles or at home cheering on her beloved New York Yankees. She has been and will continue to be an important part of our community. We wish you the best in retirement!!
